description:
Job Requirements
Fully available in the Polish time zone;
Ability to work from the office in Warsaw (weekly: 4 days at office + 1 day remotely);
Very good knowledge of Java 8+ and object-oriented programming issues;
Experience in independent design, implementation, documentation and testing of application components;
Very good and practical knowledge of Spring, Spring Boot, SQL, Scrum, Hibernate/JPA and JEE frameworks;
Practical knowledge with message queue systems, particularly RabbitMQ;
Practical knowledge of tools supporting the software development process: Maven, Git, Gitlab, Gitlab CI/CD, Jenkins, Nexus, Jira;
Knowledge of relational databases, in particular Oracle;
Practical knowledge of RESTful API design;
Experience in system integration;
Experience with distributed systems;
Experience with application servers, JBoss/WildFly;
Knowledge of scanning tools (Fortify, Sonatype..)
Knowledge of English / B2;
Nice to have:
Angular
Linux server
Docker

Akvelon is a software engineering company helping enterprise teams turn AI adoption into measurable engineering results: improving productivity, reducing inefficiencies, and moving AI initiatives from experimentation to practical production use. Our teams support large-scale software organizations, Fortune 500 companies, and leading technology platforms, including Microsoft, T-Mobile, Google, Reddit, and GitHub. We bring hands-on experience in building, modernizing, and optimizing complex software systems.
We are looking for a Senior / Lead Software Development Engineer to join the Managed Kafka Connectors initiative. The project focuses on building and improving a managed Kafka connectors ecosystem for cloud data platforms, accelerating onboarding of first-party connectors, and ensuring production readiness across reliability, performance, authentication, and cloud-specific integration requirements.
The role requires strong ownership across implementation, debugging, launch readiness, and operational quality. The engineer will work with Java-based connector workers and core connector logic, Go-based API/service integration layers, and cloud data systems such as BigQuery, Spanner, Bigtable, Iceberg, Debezium, and other source/sink connector workflows.
Requirements:
Strong Java / JVM engineering experience, including performance-sensitive backend or platform development;
Strong understanding of distributed systems and reliability principles;
Practical experience with Kafka / Kafka Connect ecosystem, connector-based systems, or data integration platforms;
Strong debugging and troubleshooting skills across infrastructure, networking, authentication, and runtime behavior;
Experience with build systems, dependency management, and large codebases;
Experience working with cloud infrastructure, preferably GCP or similar cloud environments;
Strong engineering ownership: ability to drive delivery, quality, launch readiness, and operational improvements.
Nice to Have:
Practical Go backend/service development experience for API-facing changes and service integration;
Experience with Apache Iceberg, Debezium, CDC systems, or source/sink connector integrations;
Experience with cloud data systems such as BigQuery, Spanner, Bigtable, Iceberg, or Debezium-based workflows;
Experience with SRE / operational readiness, including monitoring, probers, load testing, playbooks, and launch reviews;
Experience with OSS or large-scale platform engineering;
Strong GCP infrastructure experience.
Working Conditions:
Priority location: Krakow, Poland (or relocation to Krakow from another city);
Candidate should be ready to relocate to Krakow if not already based there;
Office presence is expected several times per week / potentially up to 5 days per week;
Required overlap: until 10 AM PST.

At least 1 year of professional experience;
Knowledge of Java 8 and Spring framework;
Strong capacity to identify requirements and define technical solutions;
Knowledge of Kafka (or at least familiar with any other queuing system);
Version control tools, especially Git;
Design patterns and clean code;
Good English level
Nice to have:
Experience with RESTful Web Services / Microservices;
Experience with automating deployment, scaling and management of containerized applications (e.g Kubernetes);
Experience with Continuous Integration / Continuous Delivery practices.
